post:
We know that our 1GB KVM VPS package for $7 per month has been on the wish list of many LET/LEB members before the end of 2012, unfortunately we were not able to meet the demand at the end of last year. To make up for it we are now bringing you not one, but three 1GB VPS plans: one is powered by KVM and two are powered by Xen virtualization. All three packages come with 1GB RAM, swap space enabled and various amounts of resources (depending on the plan).
To make this offer even better, each VPS account comes with our Free Managed DNS Service. You can host up to 500 domains per account and there is not limit for the amount of DNS queries. If you are currently using an expensive DNS hosting service that charges you an arm and a leg for everything and places a limit on the amount of DNS queries that you can have per month then you should definitively switch to us and get your DNS service for free.
And to top it all off, we also include hardware DDoS protection (at the network layer) and a 99.9% SLA for every VPS server.

Our website: http://www.vpsnodebox.com
Support email: support@vpsnodebox.com
Time in business: over 1 year (started in December 2011 as DrupalCentric.com)

We maintain our own Xen software stack (http://repo.vpsnodebox.com) and we run Xen on CentOS 6 along with our own custom Xen kernel.

For customers and members of this community, as well as other providers who wish to deploy newer software on CentOS 6 (including our own Xen software stack), please visit our public software repository at http://repo.vpsnodebox.com

